A: The problem is that you are calling dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator().next() in the loop. This means that you are always getting the first child of the snapshot, regardless of the loop iteration.
Instead, you should use the iterator you get from dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator() and call next() on that.
Here is the corrected code:
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        for (Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator(); it.hasNext(); ) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This way, you will get all the children values from the snapshot.

